				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: LDoN song lineup<a name="24002"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 8:45 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Lull
<br />
Mez
<br />
Snare
<br />
haste
<br />
mana
<br />

<br />
Those are the 5 that I keep up at all times for LDoNs.
<br />
We pull, so you need the lull.
<br />
We CC so you need mez..
<br />
Can't have mobs running away, so we snare.
<br />
We fight, so we need haste, as does the Tank.
<br />
We get requests for mana, so we play battery (ARG).
<br />

<br />
While I hate being a manabattery, I don't mind playing the song in a twist during battle if it doesn't take place of something more important.  Keeping mana flowing to cleric is a very good idea.
<br />

<br />
And be sure to let them know what songs you're going to play when in combat, and that you may drop them while playing CC if need be.  And tell the casters to make sure they stay in range of your mana song.
<br />

<br />
My 2 quarternotes on this.
<br />

<br />
For me, in LDoN, I am mele.  I am fortunate in that I have the Tear Shaped Ring for string (80% mod) and the Troubador's mace for brass.  I duel wield weapons and fight fight fight.  I only change out to lute for better string mod if we are down for a couple min for some reason.  Otherwise I'm pure weapons wielding.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">What in my name suggests I'm your mana battery?  Baroness Shassiash L'Ryckstrike, Minstral on E'ci in her 52nd Composition.</span></td>
