				<td colspan="2"><span>I use essentially the same lineup but I also have CoD and DDD up at all times. I don't do pickup groups, I usually run with my wife's beastlord and a friend's cleric, so I am always the MT. When things get nasty I try to pull every mob on myself and use sub-20% health aggro to keep my cleric alive. I'm arrogant enough to believe I will always live and confident enough in my cleric to know she will always save me. For whatever reason, it's always worked  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-3.gif" border="0" alt="Scared" hspace="2" /> It probably helps that in my bag of grouping gear I forsake most other stats for hitpoints.
<br />

<br />
Edit: For the record, I (almost) NEVER twist manasong during combat. I won't change my attitude on that until someone conclusively proves to me that the few points of mana that will be regenerated in the course of a 45-60 second fight actually makes any difference. Any caster that complains can gate. I've been known to throw in a few pulses of it across long drawn out fights, but it is a rule of thumb that my bard runs manasong during downtime only.</span></td>
